{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"efc2240e-3152-442d-8c96-3aee46df0297","content":"\n\nUse `Assert.ThrowsException<T>` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws<T>` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n}\n```\n\n**Why:**\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if *any* line throws, masking bugs\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` pinpoints the exact call that should throw\n- You can also capture the exception to assert on its message:\n\n```csharp\nvar ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n    () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\nAssert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName);\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"271881cd-39c8-4585-870a-b2541e385595","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question — no need to explore the codebase.","outputTokens":269},"id":"15f62e9d-750b-42a0-ad88-0c6793a39da7","timestamp":"2026-04-03T03:15:46.610Z","parentId":"9fd01e9a-2d99-40f1-b70c-43c830152486"}
